'''Anima Mundi''' is the life force of [[Gielinor]].{{CiteNPC |npc=Felfiz Yaryus |quote=[...] the Anima Mundi, the life force of our world.}} It has a strong connection to [[spirit tree]]s and other flora of the world, and is most alluded to by [[Gnome (race)|gnomes]].{{CiteNPC |npc=Hazelmere |loc=The Eyes of Glouphrie |quote=[...] I felt a sudden pain, as if the Anima Mundi was crying out with the loss of a favoured child.... And I knew that one of the Old Ones had died, and I had lost a friend. |name=spirit tree}}{{CiteNPC |npc=Felfiz Yaryus |quote=Here, you can grow Iasor, Kronos and Attas plants. [...] Three unique plants with a special affinity to the Anima Mundi, the life force of our world.}}{{CiteNPC |npc=Gnome Child (20th Anniversary event){{!}}Gnome Child |loc=20th Anniversary event |quote=I wish to witness the moment when the individual cabbage's connection to the Anima Mundi is irreversibly severed, as you pluck it from the nurturing soil in the field south of Falador. |name=cabbage}} Anima is fed by life.{{CiteNPC |npc=Kaal-Xil-Dar |quote=The anima of this world, it is fed by life. |name=life}}

The [[Tasakaal]] took on the purpose of serving the balance between life and death to protect the anima of Gielinor. According to them, without life there is no anima, but because life can also destroy and endanger the anima, it must be kept under control.{{NamedRef|life}}{{CiteNPC |npc=Tasakaal |quote=
* '''Kaal-Mej-San:''' Without life, there is no anima.
* '''Kaal-Ket-Jor:''' But life can also destroy. It can endanger the anima.
* '''Kaal-Xil-Dar:''' So life must be kept in check.
* '''Kaal-Mej-San:''' This is our purpose.}}

When [[Argento]] was killed, [[Hazelmere]] felt a sudden pain, believing it to be the Anima Mundi crying out for the death of the spirit tree.{{NamedRef|spirit tree}}

According to a [[Gnome Child (20th Anniversary event)|gnome child]], the Anima Mundi works in mysterious ways.{{CiteNPC |npc=Gnome Child (20th Anniversary event){{!}}Gnome Child |loc=20th Anniversary event |quote=Some forces in this world move in mysterious ways. Gravity, the Anima Mundi and the price of granite mauls are just three everyday examples.}} He also states that when a [[cabbage]] is plucked from the soil, its connection to the Anima Mundi is irreversibly severed.{{NamedRef|cabbage}}

